148
00:12:53,124 --> 00:12:54,340
(The Travels of Lao Can)

149
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,620
(On Our Salvation)

150
00:12:56,516 --> 00:12:57,188
(Prequel to the Eternal Peace)

151
00:12:57,188 --> 00:12:58,720
(On the Young China)

152
00:13:01,444 --> 00:13:03,104
(Illustrated Flowers in the Mirror,
Volume Three)

153
00:13:07,812 --> 00:13:09,312
(Revolutionary Strategy
of the Tongmenghui)

154
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:15,264
(Sent by Wu Lanshan, Inscribed by Yunji)

155
00:13:17,892 --> 00:13:24,160
(Ideas and revolutionaries never die.
Peilun's spirit urges us onward.)

156
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,519
Who exactly are you?

157
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:51,240
(Sent by Wu Lanshan, Inscribed by Yunji)
He was also my comrade.

158
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:52,840
Do you know Yunji?

159
00:13:56,159 --> 00:14:01,759
Yu Peilun, courtesy name Yunji,
went to study in Japan seven years ago.

160
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:07,480
He and I joined
the Tongmenghui together.

161
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:18,399
Just last month, the Guangzhou uprising
failed and Yunji was captured.

162
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:22,240
He chose death over surrender.

163
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:28,919
Ideas and revolutionaries never die.

164
00:14:30,759 --> 00:14:34,159
That was what he said at his trial.

165
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:48,159
Comrade Peilun
gave me this book last year.

166
00:14:49,159 --> 00:14:52,399
By the time I heard from him again,
he was no longer alive.

167
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,200
These words were what I wrote
upon learning of his martyrdom.

168
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:01,200
Comrade? You are a prince's daughter,

169
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:04,960
a Beiyang general's wife,
but you are a member of the Tongmenghui?

170
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:15,879
Has Muqing also joined the Tongmenghui?

171
00:15:34,879 --> 00:15:37,799
Seems these people have
no idea who hired them.

172
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,920
It doesn't matter. Who else could it be
besides the Japanese?

173
00:15:43,639 --> 00:15:46,879
It must be that woman Sei I Shinpu
or one of her subordinates.

174
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,000
I'll go confront them.

175
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,799
Muqing, those are Japanese.

176
00:15:56,799 --> 00:15:57,799
So what?

177
00:15:57,799 --> 00:16:02,799
It's best not to take action
against foreigners these days.

178
00:16:02,799 --> 00:16:05,720
Mr. Cunqing always warns us
not to provoke them.

179
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,440
Okay, I will ask Mr. Cunqing.

180
00:16:11,159 --> 00:16:14,120
Muqing, should these just be locked up?

181
00:16:15,679 --> 00:16:17,039
Why should we continue to do that?

182
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:19,840
No need to waste food on those
who help the Japanese deal with us.

183
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,320
Have those newcomers
who haven't interrogated suspects

184
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:25,040
use them for practice until their death.

185
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:29,240
During my search for the Altar Treasure,

186
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:31,200
the Japanese have been interfering.

187
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,519
Their head is called Sei I Shinpu.

188
00:16:32,519 --> 00:16:36,559
They've ambushed us several times,
followed us and even tried to murder us.

189
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:38,440
So rampant. It's intolerable.

190
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:41,200
I ask for your permission
to take action against them.

191
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,440
How will you do it?

192
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:48,240
Once you permit, I'll secretly kill
Sei I Shinpu and her party tonight.

193
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,679
And then?

194
00:16:50,679 --> 00:16:52,519
I can make it look like an accident.

195
00:16:55,279 --> 00:16:59,639
So Muqing keeps you close
because you know

196
00:16:59,639 --> 00:17:01,519
the secrets of the Futu Temple.

197
00:17:01,519 --> 00:17:04,279
And because he couldn't watch
over you all the time,

198
00:17:04,279 --> 00:17:05,680
he sent you to me.

199
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:11,519
Men Sandao,
that imperial lackey. He used me.

200
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:14,119
I'll arrange
for your departure immediately.

201
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:16,799
Don't worry.
I will ensure your safe departure.

202
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,359
Are you heading to Hong Kong or Japan?

203
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:20,759
No, I can't go.

204
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:22,799
No?

205
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:25,519
Do you know what you are now?

206
00:17:26,279 --> 00:17:28,799
You are an imperial convict and a rebel.

207
00:17:28,799 --> 00:17:30,920
You could be taken to Caishikou
for execution at any moment.

208
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,640
Listen to me. Leave immediately.
I will deal with Men Sandao.

209
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:37,840
He can't stop me.

210
00:17:40,039 --> 00:17:44,359
First, listen to me. The last wish
of the owner of the Altar Treasure

211
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:46,640
is to bestow it upon the Tongmenghui.

212
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,880
My mission returning home
this time is to protect this clue

213
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:49,920
and assist with the liaison.

214
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,960
Tan Xian has already been sacrificed.

215
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:55,000
The Qing Imperial Court, the Beiyang
and the Japanese all want it.

216
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,720
No matter which party gets the treasure,

217
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,960
it will betray the hard work
of many people

218
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,440
and even let down the treasure protector
who has suffered for years.

219
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,440
So I must stay.
I must find the treasure.

220
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:10,320
And I mustn't go.
I mustn't leave Mr. Mu.

221
00:18:11,119 --> 00:18:12,480
You can't leave Muqing?

222
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:13,800
No.

223
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,480
Why?

224
00:18:16,599 --> 00:18:18,240
At the Futu Temple,

225
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,759
Mr. Mu had no choice but to inherit
the legacy of the Bodhi Department.

226
00:18:20,759 --> 00:18:23,319
But he has absolutely no idea
where the seal is.

227
00:18:23,319 --> 00:18:26,440
You have the passphrase,
so only you know.

228
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,800
It's of great importance.
I cannot tell you for now.

229
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,920
But I cannot leave Mr. Mu
before the treasure is found.

230
00:18:34,559 --> 00:18:40,440
I understand. What can I do to help you?

231
00:18:41,799 --> 00:18:44,039
You're already helping me
by letting me stay here.

232
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:47,880
That doesn't count. I'm helping
Men Sandao, the imperial hound.

233
00:18:51,279 --> 00:18:55,200
Princess, actually I feel
that Mr. Mu is not the usual hound.

234
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:58,480
After he found out
I was from the Tongmenghui,

235
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,880
he didn't send me to the prison.

236
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,759
Nor did he interrogate me
by torturing me severely.

237
00:19:01,759 --> 00:19:04,519
He even showed
understanding of my actions.

238
00:19:04,519 --> 00:19:07,759
I think he understands revolution
and sympathizes with revolutionaries.

239
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:14,480
Yes, Muqing participated in the reform
with the late Emperor in the past.

240
00:19:16,119 --> 00:19:17,960
He's not the kind of person
with outdated thinking.

241
00:19:19,759 --> 00:19:23,440
During this time, I've had discussions
with Mr. Mu about democracy and reform.

242
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,960
I've found

243
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:27,759
he's not like those decadent and blind
loyalists of the Qing Imperial Court.

244
00:19:27,759 --> 00:19:29,640
He is open to revolutionary ideas.

245
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,519
We can pull him to our camp.

246
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:35,280
If we can persuade him
to join us and help us,

247
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,480
our chances of success
will greatly increase.

248
00:19:39,039 --> 00:19:40,839
You want to lobby him to join us?

249
00:19:40,839 --> 00:19:41,640
What do you think?

250
00:19:46,119 --> 00:19:48,839
I've never talked
about these things with Muqing before.

251
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:54,119
But one thing you need to know
is that Muqing is a Manchu.

252
00:19:54,119 --> 00:19:56,400
He could accept
the late Emperor's wish for reforms.

253
00:19:56,920 --> 00:20:00,720
If it's the Tongmenghui conducting
the revolution, he may not agree.

254
00:20:02,359 --> 00:20:03,880
Aren't you a Manchu too?

255
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:10,400
I... I returned from studying abroad.

256
00:20:25,799 --> 00:20:27,440
Wang Jialuo is the Dharma inheritor?

257
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:33,400
Is it a coincidence or fate?

258
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,776
Whether it's a coincidence or fate,

259
00:20:36,359 --> 00:20:38,640
he doesn't seem to be of much use.

260
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,799
He doesn't have any seals at all

261
00:20:40,799 --> 00:20:43,319
or know what the Dharma Seal is.

262
00:20:43,319 --> 00:20:46,039
Not necessarily.
Since he's an inheritor,

263
00:20:46,039 --> 00:20:48,192
he might be able
to get what others cannot.

264
00:20:48,759 --> 00:20:52,559
Second thing, on the 6th of next month,
Southern Shaolin inheritors will go

265
00:20:52,559 --> 00:20:55,119
to the Baohe Inn to fulfill
a 30-year-old promise.

266
00:20:55,119 --> 00:20:58,440
If nothing unexpected happens, it'll be
the day the four inheritors meet.

267
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,880
The four seals will come together?

268
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:03,039
I don't know if they will all go.

269
00:21:03,039 --> 00:21:05,160
It's uncertain
whether they can all be gathered.

270
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:08,480
The Discipline and Bodhi Seals
are with Zhuo Bufan and Men Sandao.

271
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:11,680
Both of them will definitely go.
Mr. Wang will go too.

272
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:13,039
But he doesn't have a seal.

273
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:19,000
The key point is the fourth person,
related to the treasure, may attend.

274
00:21:20,119 --> 00:21:22,400
Where is the Baohe Inn?

275
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:26,039
Men Sandao is on it, using
lots of resources from the Department,

276
00:21:26,039 --> 00:21:27,039
so he'll probably find it.

277
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,200
And the third one?

278
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,480
Mr. Wang has the same tattoo

279
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:41,119
as his crazy old master.

280
00:21:41,119 --> 00:21:43,599
I think it may be a sect inheritance.

281
00:21:43,599 --> 00:21:45,160
But perhaps it's not that simple.

282
00:21:45,799 --> 00:21:51,160
The tattoo might be a map or a seal.

283
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,520
This doubt must be investigated.

284
00:21:53,359 --> 00:21:56,599
I need a mini camera to take
a photo of the tattoo on him.

285
00:21:56,599 --> 00:21:58,240
Still Expo. I've used it before.

286
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:01,400
Okay. You take the photo
and I'll have an expert analyze it.

287
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:04,920
If there is any hidden information,
it will definitely be found.

288
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,320
Have you already convinced Mr. Wang?

289
00:22:12,559 --> 00:22:16,559
He is an extremely conservative man
who values traditional customs.

290
00:22:16,559 --> 00:22:18,400
But he is also a man.

291
00:22:36,359 --> 00:22:40,240
Kill them, and you'll be relieved.
But trouble will come to me.

292
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:46,000
Muqing, the Japanese
nowadays cannot be provoked.

293
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,839
Today is different from before.
The situation is too sensitive.

294
00:22:50,839 --> 00:22:54,359
Not just the Japanese,
but also the Germans and the British.

295
00:22:54,359 --> 00:22:56,920
Those foreigners are all untouchable.

296
00:22:56,920 --> 00:23:01,079
Once they make a fuss using the death
of their nationals in the capital,

297
00:23:01,799 --> 00:23:04,240
that would be an issue.

298
00:23:05,519 --> 00:23:09,160
We might have to cede territory
and pay compensation. It's not worth it.

299
00:23:10,759 --> 00:23:17,319
Hold it in. We must hold it in.
Continue to hold it in.

300
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,799
How can we change
what the foreigners have decided?

301
00:23:22,799 --> 00:23:27,759
This is the Concession. You have
no right to enforce the law here.

302
00:23:30,599 --> 00:23:32,160
They forfeited territories
and paid indemnities every year!

303
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:46,599
Sir, take care. Please come often.

304
00:24:12,599 --> 00:24:18,079
It is dry. Be on alert for fires.

305
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:27,104
It is dry. Be on alert for fires.

306
00:24:27,104 --> 00:24:27,680
(Tea)

307
00:24:30,799 --> 00:24:32,640
You can't come in here. Go away.

308
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:35,519
Ask Sei I Shinpu out to see me.

309
00:24:35,519 --> 00:24:36,279
Who are you?

310
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:39,400
Your father. Tell Sei I Shinpu
to come out to see me.

311
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,119
Asking for death.

312
00:24:48,759 --> 00:24:49,599
You failed again?

313
00:24:50,759 --> 00:24:54,480
We sent 17 people,
but all of them disappeared.

314
00:24:58,279 --> 00:25:00,079
What do you mean by all disappeared?

315
00:25:00,079 --> 00:25:02,880
No one can be found. No traces at all.

316
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,200
Sei I Shinpu, come out to see me.

317
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:12,039
How come it's him again?
We've all been avoiding him.

318
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:19,960
The back door. This is our place.
He wouldn't cause trouble here.

319
00:25:28,279 --> 00:25:30,839
Sei I Shinpu,
come out, or I'm coming in.

320
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,400
Are you deaf? Didn't you hear me?

321
00:25:57,400 --> 00:26:00,400
Mr. Muqing, you honor us
with your presence.

322
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:02,920
I really should change my clothes
before coming out to see you.

323
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:06,559
Are you a working girl?
Having special clothes to meet guests?

324
00:26:06,559 --> 00:26:09,400
How dare you be so rude?
What do you mean?

325
00:26:12,839 --> 00:26:14,880
It's his first time here.

326
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,440
We must observe proper etiquette.

327
00:26:17,119 --> 00:26:19,599
Right, Mr. Muqing?

328
00:26:19,599 --> 00:26:21,839
A servant shouldn't really

329
00:26:21,839 --> 00:26:24,000
interrupt when their master is speaking.

330
00:26:24,759 --> 00:26:26,839
Let her slap herself.

331
00:26:26,839 --> 00:26:28,440
I shall forgive her for her words.

332
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:31,279
Otherwise, I will be the one
to deliver the slap.

333
00:26:31,279 --> 00:26:34,279
Mr. Muqing,
this is the Japanese embassy.

334
00:26:34,279 --> 00:26:37,359
If you're here for tea and conversation,
we will treat you with courtesy.

335
00:26:37,359 --> 00:26:39,000
I've smashed the door for you,

336
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:40,880
and you think I came here
to drink tea and chat?

337
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:43,359
As a high-ranking official
of the Department,

338
00:26:43,359 --> 00:26:45,920
you know the consequences
of trespassing in our embassy.

339
00:26:49,559 --> 00:26:52,559
Do you know the consequences of killing
an official of the Department?

340
00:26:53,599 --> 00:26:56,279
Do you know the consequences
of assassinating a prince?

341
00:26:56,279 --> 00:26:59,960
You hired 17 people to ambush
outside the prince's residence,

342
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:02,640
intending to assassinate Prince Qi.
The proof is solid.

343
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:06,176
Even if I kill all of you,
who can do anything to me?

344
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:08,480
If there is irrefutable evidence,

345
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:11,759
I'm afraid we'd already
be surrounded by your people.

346
00:27:11,759 --> 00:27:15,279
You came alone. Doesn't that mean
you have no evidence?

347
00:27:15,279 --> 00:27:16,880
So what if you've captured them?

348
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,960
They are all the locals.

349
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:22,920
How do you prove
they are not framing me? Stop him.

350
00:27:46,799 --> 00:27:49,952
I said it. If you don't do it yourself,
I will do the slapping

351
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:56,359
Evidence is something
that can be produced at any time.

352
00:27:56,359 --> 00:27:58,480
As long as I wish, I can arrest
your people for interrogation.

353
00:27:58,480 --> 00:27:59,800
Even if I say you are a man,

354
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:01,960
they all have to say yes obediently.

355
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:04,720
How many of the people
you sent to follow me have returned?

356
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:08,480
You know I am the one
who killed your people. What can you do?

357
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:11,480
If I now execute you all,
what can you do?

358
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:15,160
You're great, disregarding the relations
between our two countries.

359
00:28:15,799 --> 00:28:18,799
Relations? You've got
the nerve to mention them.

360
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:21,240
If you hadn't provoked me,
would I have even glanced at you?

361
00:28:22,079 --> 00:28:26,880
Sei I Shinpu, I don't want
to see any of you again.

362
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:32,400
Remember what I said,
or next time it won't just be a slap.

363
00:28:41,359 --> 00:28:43,119
I must kill him.

364
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,880
You've been toiling for days.
Eat it to replenish yourself.

365
00:28:50,799 --> 00:28:53,319
I really can't eat it anymore.
Aren't you sleepy?

366
00:28:53,319 --> 00:28:57,559
No. After so long,
I've finally seen a comrade.

367
00:28:57,559 --> 00:28:58,960
I'm too excited to feel tired.

368
00:29:01,279 --> 00:29:02,680
I'm not like you.

369
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:05,240
Yunji never allowed me
to participate in any activities.

370
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:08,119
He said my identity was special,
and that it was best to hide it

371
00:29:08,119 --> 00:29:09,799
and let it play a role
at a crucial moment.

372
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,520
So I'm usually just idling around

373
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,799
and doing nothing.

374
00:29:16,559 --> 00:29:18,759
That's why I especially hope
to do something.

375
00:29:22,519 --> 00:29:24,640
You previously traced it to Fujian?

376
00:29:26,319 --> 00:29:28,400
The Southern Shaolin was in Fujian too?

377
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:29,560
Yes.

378
00:29:30,519 --> 00:29:34,440
I think it is very likely related
to my father and Zhong Haichao.

379
00:29:36,039 --> 00:29:36,759
Why?

380
00:29:37,319 --> 00:29:40,680
Zhong Haichao used to be responsible
for the Beiyang troops in the capital.

381
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:42,519
That is an important position.

382
00:29:42,519 --> 00:29:45,880
But my father has pulled some strings
to have him transferred to Fujian.

383
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,556
I didn't pay attention to it.

384
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:51,200
Now that I think about it,
could it be for the secret treasure?

385
00:29:52,119 --> 00:29:53,160
When is he going?

386
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:54,240
Leaving in the next few days.

387
00:29:55,759 --> 00:29:58,720
Once he leaves,
we'll be much more at ease.

388
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,640
You and your husband...

389
00:30:04,799 --> 00:30:09,000
Why don't you and your husband
seem very close?

390
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:15,520
I am the daughter of a prince.

391
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:19,799
I had no choice in my marriage at all.

392
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:33,952
Didn't you ask me before
why I knew Muqing a lot?

393
00:30:36,260 --> 00:30:39,076
He and I are each other's first love.

394
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:46,800
(We met when Muqing
was the late Emperor's guard.)

395
00:30:48,039 --> 00:30:51,519
(But because of the difference
in social status, we didn't speak out.)

396
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:10,519
(Muqing accidentally dropped the sachet
he made for me in front of His Majesty.)

397
00:31:11,079 --> 00:31:12,359
(The late Emperor saw it.)

398
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:14,960
(The late Emperor came
to know about our thing.)

399
00:31:17,119 --> 00:31:18,920
(The late Emperor was always fond of me)

400
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:21,720
(and appreciated Muqing the most.)

401
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:26,040
His Majesty said, "Now that the reform
is underway, what does status matter?"

402
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,039
But to make it acceptable to my father,

403
00:31:29,039 --> 00:31:33,480
the late Emperor first promoted
Muqing from third rank to second rank

404
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:36,640
and said after the reform,
he would be promoted to first rank.

405
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:39,200
And he acted as a matchmaker for us.

406
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:44,559
(And then the reform began.)

407
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:54,119
(The Hundred Days' Reform
failed, and then...)

408
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,920
And there was no "after that".

409
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:07,960
Not long after, my father
arranged a marriage for me.

410
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:12,040
Zhong Haichao is the man he chose.

411
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:41,440
Muqing.

412
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,040
I am not a woman
from an ordinary family.

413
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:51,519
I need to see the bigger picture,

414
00:32:51,519 --> 00:32:53,119
so I cannot have a choice.

415
00:32:54,920 --> 00:33:00,120
I'll marry a general
and, like me, he has studied abroad.

416
00:33:00,839 --> 00:33:04,640
He is the youngest leader
in the Beiyang Army and is promising.

417
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:07,400
The country is increasingly unstable.

418
00:33:08,279 --> 00:33:10,960
The power of civil officials
is getting weaker and less significant.

419
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:15,760
Military generals are gaining more
and more say, especially the Beiyang.

420
00:33:16,599 --> 00:33:19,720
The Beiyang Army is the most elite army.

421
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,519
I am a princess. He is a military man.

422
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:28,160
This is very crucial
for the future political landscape.

423
00:33:31,519 --> 00:33:34,920
You may never leave this prison
for the rest of your life.

424
00:33:36,279 --> 00:33:37,519
I must forget you.

425
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:43,280
There's nothing time can't erase.
The same goes for you.

426
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,000
The most fleeting things in life

427
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:51,920
are the youth that never returns
and the falling blossoms.

428
00:33:55,279 --> 00:33:57,400
If one day you regain your freedom,

429
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,760
I hope by then
you will have gotten over me.

430
00:34:28,599 --> 00:34:30,760
What an awful era.

431
00:34:31,559 --> 00:34:33,880
Muqing hates nothing more
than Yuan Shikai and the Beiyang Army.

432
00:34:35,079 --> 00:34:39,239
But I had to marry
a Beiyang Army officer.

433
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:44,840
It's not hard to imagine
how much Muqing must be suffering.

434
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:54,560
I am a Manchu.
Why would I join the Tongmenghui?

435
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:59,559
Because I hate everything
I've experienced and yet I'm helpless.

436
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:04,320
Until I met Yunji,
who showed me those books.

437
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:10,320
He made me understand
I could just let time erase everything.

438
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:11,920
I could also struggle, resist

439
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:16,480
and destroy this era
that won't allow us to be ourselves.

440
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:20,640
I am a Manchu
and the daughter of a prince.

441
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,520
I had no choice over my birth.

442
00:35:24,119 --> 00:35:26,519
Joining the Tongmenghui was my choice.

443
00:35:26,519 --> 00:35:30,079
It was my first true choice.

444
00:35:38,039 --> 00:35:40,840
Would Mr. Mu think the same as you?

445
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,040
I hope he can.

446
00:35:45,559 --> 00:35:46,880
If you can persuade him,

447
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,920
I think our chances
of success would be very high.

448
00:35:51,639 --> 00:35:52,719
I can give it a try.

449
00:35:57,400 --> 00:36:00,840
By the way, do you know
that Mr. Mu has a tattoo on his body?

450
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:02,400
The abbot of the Futu Temple

451
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:04,600
allowed him inside
because he saw the tattoo.

452
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:10,320
That tattoo depicts intertwined pigeons,

453
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,800
venomous snakes and pigs.

454
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,840
Why would he get such a tattoo?

455
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:16,384
I asked him, but he didn't know.

456
00:36:16,384 --> 00:36:18,679
He told me his master
gave him the tattoo.

457
00:36:18,679 --> 00:36:20,960
Perhaps it's a reminder
for him to always reflect on himself.

458
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,079
What's wrong with that tattoo?

459
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:29,719
It's nothing.

460
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:33,719
I just don't know why the abbot
was so sure that he was the inheritor

461
00:36:33,719 --> 00:36:36,039
of the Bodhi Department
after seeing that tattoo.

462
00:36:36,039 --> 00:36:38,360
Maybe it's the mark of their sect.

463
00:36:41,679 --> 00:36:44,960
His master wished for reform.

464
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,599
The late Emperor wished for reform.

465
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:51,440
I think Muqing will side with us.

466
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:55,239
He is someone we must win over.

467
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:06,440
Time flies. It's almost dawn.

468
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:13,120
Yes, it's about to be daylight.

469
00:37:15,556 --> 00:37:18,560
(The 26th day of the 4th month in Year 3 of Xuantong Era.
Grain in Ear is 14 days away.)

470
